  "title": "Fleet Operations Executive",
  "description": "<p>1. Fleet Operations & Management</p><p>- Logistics & Prep: Track vehicle movements, optimize parking, and oversee vehicle preparation (servicing, repairs, and quality checks) for delivery.</p><p>- Maintenance: Inspect vehicles, assess bodywork, obtain repair quotes, and maintain overall fleet roadworthiness and cleanliness.</p><p>- Workshop Coordination: Monitor workshop progress, approve repairs, and minimize vehicle downtime.</p><p>2. Customer Service & Accident Management</p><p>- Customer Support: Act as the main contact for servicing, breakdowns, and vehicle replacements.</p><p>- Operations: Coordinate vehicle handovers and swaps</p><p>efficiently.</p><p>- Accident Handling: Guide customers through accident reporting, manage insurance claims, and coordinate repairs.</p><p>- Relationships: Maintain strong ties with clients and external partners.</p><p>3. Administrative & Reporting</p><p>- Data Entry: Keep fleet records accurate and up to date in internal systems.</p><p>- Reporting: Generate weekly and monthly operational reports for management.</p><p>- General Support: Assist with ad-hoc operational tasks as needed.</p>",
